getTerminals

public static java.util.List<Node> getTerminals(java.util.List<Node> syntax)
Returns those nodes from the given syntax that have an arity of 0. The given List is not modified at all.

Parameters:
syntax - a List of Nodes. The syntax must not be null.
Returns:
a List of those Node objects that have an arity of 0.

intRange

public static java.util.List<Literal> intRange(int start,
                                               int interval,
                                               int quantity)
Creates a List of Literal objects with a range of values. Given a start parameter of 2, a quantity of 4 and an interval of 3, the returned List will contain 4 literals with the values: 2, 5, 8, 11.

Parameters:
start - the value that should be used for the first Literal in the range.
interval - the interval between each element of the range.
quantity - the number of elements in the range. Must be zero or greater.
Returns:
a List of Literals with the range of values given.

createVariables

public static java.util.List<Variable> createVariables(java.lang.Class<?> datatype,
                                                       java.lang.String... variableNames)
Creates a List of Variable objects of the given data type. The number of variables created will be the same as the number of variable names provided. The variables will have a null value.

Parameters:
datatype - the data-type for all the variables to be created.
variableNames - the names to assign to each of the variables.
Returns:
a List of Variables with the given names.
